| NASA Gears Up for the Regolith Rumble                              |
|   from the in-this-corner-weighing-in-at-0.34-pounds dept.         |
|   posted by Zonk on Saturday May 12, @05:39 (NASA)                 |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/12/0654212      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]eldavojohn writes "NASA is holding [1]another scientific challenge to
see which autonomous robot can [2]move the most regolith in 30 minutes.
The finer details: 'To win the cash prizes for NASA's Regolith Challenge,
teams must demonstrate fully autonomous robots capable of collecting at
least 330 pounds (150 kilograms) of mock Moon dirt within 30 minutes.
Whichever robot moves the most regolith over the benchmark limit, while
still meeting contest specifications, wins, NASA said. But in order to
compete, lunar regolith excavators must weigh less than 88 pounds (40
kilograms) and run on less than 30 kilowatts of power, according to
contest rules.'"

