|   from the that's-master-chief-to-you dept.                        |
|   posted by Zonk on Saturday May 12, @13:27 (XBox (Games))         |
|   http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/12/1655205        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Yesterday in New York City Microsoft held an invite-only [0]preview of
the Halo 3 Beta, and passed out early Beta keys to a group of game
journalists. The result is a [1]barrage of coverage about this
most-anticipated title. Notable features beyond basic previews include
[2]Dan Hsu's take on the game, [3]Dean Takahashi's 'I got my butt kicked'
perspective, the San Jose Merc's [4]interview with Bungie Community Lead
Brian Jarrad, CVG's hosting of the [5]official Beta Movie, and Joystiq's
[6]interview with Frank O'Connor, Bungie's writing lead. From the 1up
preview: "It's unmistakably Halo gameplay, despite the rearranged
controls (which feel natural after 10 minutes), and all of the additions
fit perfectly into the multiplayer universe we've come to love. The
interface has been overhauled and is even easier to use, and you now have
such niceties as being able to change your control layout at any point on
any screen. While the visuals are rich and beautiful, it's the audio
that's really impressed us so far. The rumbling throttle of unleashing
dual SMGs makes them feel incredibly powerful, and the Spartan Laser
tearing past your head is as scary as you'd imagine. Audio cues are more
important than ever, and the better your sound system the more next-gen
this will feel." More coverage below.

