raguirre writes "An article on Physorg.org reports that a newly found
start [0]may be as old as the universe itself. Recent studies have
concluded that the Big Bang occurred somewhere in the neighborhood of
13.7 Billion years ago. The star, a heavy-elements laden fossil labeled
HE 1523-0901 on charts was probably born right around the same time;
approximately 13.2 Billion years ago. 'Today, astronomer Anna Frebel of
the the University of Texas at Austin McDonald Observatory and her
colleagues have deduced the star's age based on the amounts of
radioactive elements it contains compared to certain other "anchor"
elements, specifically europium, osmium and iridium.'"

